From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Juan Manuel Lopez Carrillo <juanmanuellopezcarrillo@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] watchdog: sunxi_wdt: per-variant restart priority

On the T527/sun55iw3 the vendor ATF's PSCI SYSTEM_RESET hangs without
returning, and at the default restart-handler priority (128, below the PSCI
handler's 129) the sunxi watchdog handler never ran -- so `reboot` froze the
board. Raise the priority above PSCI, but only where the variant asks for it,
via a new restart_priority field in struct sunxi_wdt_reg (sun55i = 200). Other
SoCs (A64/H3/H6...) keep the vanilla behaviour where PSCI wins.

Adopted for the Trimui Smart Pro S: forward-ported to v7.2 and squashed from the
ut-slayer/orangepi-4a-mainline series (patches 0019 + 0079). Needs
CONFIG_SUNXI_WATCHDOG built in for the restart handler to be present.
Compile-verified (drivers/watchdog/sunxi_wdt.o).

Signed-off-by: Juan Manuel Lopez Carrillo <juanmanuellopezcarrillo@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Midgy BALON <midgy971@gmail.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/watchdog/sunxi_wdt.c b/drivers/watchdog/sunxi_wdt.c
index b6c761acc..7188d01f7 100644
--- a/drivers/watchdog/sunxi_wdt.c
+++ b/drivers/watchdog/sunxi_wdt.c
@@ -48,6 +48,12 @@ struct sunxi_wdt_reg {
 	u8 wdt_reset_mask;
 	u8 wdt_reset_val;
 	u32 wdt_key_val;
+	/*
+	 * Prioridad del restart handler. 0 = por defecto (128, pierde contra
+	 * PSCI 129). En SoCs cuyo firmware EL3 cuelga en SYSTEM_RESET (T527:
+	 * ATF BSP) hay que ganar a PSCI para que `reboot` funcione.
+	 */
+	int restart_priority;
 };
 
 struct sunxi_wdt_dev {
@@ -244,6 +250,7 @@ static const struct sunxi_wdt_reg sun55i_wdt_reg = {
 	.wdt_reset_mask = 0x03,
 	.wdt_reset_val = 0x01,
 	.wdt_key_val = 0x16aa0000,
+	.restart_priority = 200,
 };
 
 static const struct of_device_id sunxi_wdt_dt_ids[] = {
@@ -282,7 +289,17 @@ static int sunxi_wdt_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	watchdog_init_timeout(&sunxi_wdt->wdt_dev, timeout, dev);
 	watchdog_set_nowayout(&sunxi_wdt->wdt_dev, nowayout);
-	watchdog_set_restart_priority(&sunxi_wdt->wdt_dev, 128);
+	/*
+	 * Prioridad > 129 (la del handler PSCI) SOLO donde la variante lo
+	 * pide: en el T527/OPi4A el SYSTEM_RESET del ATF BSP se cuelga sin
+	 * retornar, y con la prioridad estandar (128 < 129) este handler
+	 * nunca llegaba a ejecutarse -> `reboot` congelaba la placa. El BSP
+	 * 5.15 tambien resetea via watchdog. Los demas SoCs (A64/H3/H6...)
+	 * conservan el comportamiento vanilla (PSCI gana).
+	 */
+	if (sunxi_wdt->wdt_regs->restart_priority)
+		watchdog_set_restart_priority(&sunxi_wdt->wdt_dev,
+					      sunxi_wdt->wdt_regs->restart_priority);
 
 	watchdog_set_drvdata(&sunxi_wdt->wdt_dev, sunxi_wdt);
 
